The police in Katsina State on Monday paraded a Niger Republic national, Haruna Yusuf, and his two sons for alleged banditry and gunrunning. The police commissioner in Katsina, Sanusi Buba, said Mr Yusuf, 47, a resident of Muduru village in Mani Local Government Area of Katsina, led a syndicate supplying arms from Niger Republic to bandits in Zamfara and Katsina. <img data-attachment-id="438665" data-permalink="https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/more-news/438661-photos-police-arrest-suspected-niger-republic-arms-dealer-sons-in-katsina.html/attachment/ammunition-recovered-from-the-bandits" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2021/01/Ammunition-recovered-from-the-bandits.jpg?fit=1040%2C780&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="1040,780" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Ammunition recovered from the bandits" data-image-description="&lt;p&gt;Ammunition recovered from the bandits&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2021/01/Ammunition-recovered-from-the-bandits.jpg?fit=465%2C349&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2021/01/Ammunition-recovered-from-the-bandits.jpg?fit=1040%2C780&amp;ssl=1" class="size-full wp-image-438665" src="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2021/01/Ammunition-recovered-from-the-bandits.jpg?ssl=1" alt="Ammunition recovered from the bandits" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2021/01/Ammunition-recovered-from-the-bandits.jpg?w=1040&amp;ssl=1 1040w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2021/01/Ammunition-recovered-from-the-bandits.jpg?resize=465%2C349&amp;ssl=1 465w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2021/01/Ammunition-recovered-from-the-bandits.jpg?resize=768%2C576&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2021/01/Ammunition-recovered-from-the-bandits.jpg?resize=750%2C563&amp;ssl=1 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Mr Buba said the suspect was arrested alongside his sons, Ibrahim Salisu, 20, and Shuaibu Haruna, 18. Other suspected members of the syndicate paraded were Haruna Yusuf, 47, of Sawarya village, Kaita LGA of Katsina State; Haruna Adamu, 35, and Auwal Abubakar, 28, both of Maduru village, Mani LGA of Katsina. The police boss said Mr Yusuf had confessed to sourcing arms and ammunition from Niger Republic for Lawan Zayyana, Haruna Adamu and Auwal Abubakar who supply them to bandits in the forest. “He confessed to have sold over 10,000 arms and ammunition to bandits in the forest. <img data-attachment-id="438663" data-permalink="https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/more-news/438661-photos-police-arrest-suspected-niger-republic-arms-dealer-sons-in-katsina.html/attachment/machine-gun-recovered-from-the-bandits" data-orig-file="https://i1.wp.com/media.